    • Constructor Detail

      • TransactionHistoryItem

        public TransactionHistoryItem(java.util.Date transactionDate,
                              double transactionAmount,
                              java.lang.String sourceActionString,
                              java.lang.String transactionSource,
                              double sourceOriginal,
                              double sourceUpdated,
                              java.lang.String destinationActionString,
                              java.lang.String transactionDestination,
                              double destinationOriginal,
                              double destinationUpdated,
                              boolean sourceCanShowChange,
                              boolean destinationCanShowChange)
        Constructor for a TransactionHistoryItem
        Parameters:
        transactionDate - - the date this transaction occurred on
        transactionAmount - - the amount involved in the transaction, that moved from source to destination
        sourceActionString - - an action word/phrase describing the movement "from" source
        transactionSource - - a string representation of source
        sourceOriginal - - if applicable (i.e. source can show change is set) then should be set to the value of source before the transaction occurred
        sourceUpdated - - if applicable (i.e. source can show change is set) then should be set to the value of source after the transaction occurred
        destinationActionString - - an action word/phrase describing the movement "to" the destination
        transactionDestination - - a string representation of the destination
        destinationOriginal - - if applicable (i.e. destination can show change is set) then should be set to the value of destination before the transaction occurred
        destinationUpdated - - if applicable (i.e. destination can show change is set) then should be set to the value of destination after the transaction occurred
        sourceCanShowChange - - true if it makes sense to show a change in the source's value (i.e. accounts but not gains)
        destinationCanShowChange - - true if it make sense to show a change in the destination's value (i.e. savings accounts but not losses) The general format should make sense using the passed parameters: transactionAmount sourceActionString source(sourceOriginal->sourceUpdated) destinationActionString transactionDestination(destinationOriginal->destinationUpdated) Examples: 500 from Cash(1000->500) to Emergency(0->500) 500 from Cash(1000->500) payed to Chase Credit(700->200) 200 from Job deposited into Checking(300->500)
